text: Sean Dollman (born December 8, 1968 in Cape Town, Western Cape, South Africa) is a retired Irish long distance runner. He represented Ireland in two Olympics, running the 10,000 metres in 1992 and 1996.Sean Dollman Bio, Stats, and Results | Olympics at Sports-Reference.com He was the 1991 NCAA Cross Country Champion while representing Western Kentucky University and was the sixth placer finisher the year before. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1968 births Category:Irish male long-distance runners Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic athletes of Ireland
